Res or don't res, your perogative. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#222222><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/btherathetravelagency.showUserPublicProfile?gid=toricseerson>Toric Seerson</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mirth's Virtue - GL</span><br>  Posts: 242<br> <font color=#00FFFF>(4/30/03 4:43 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1167.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: MAkeing PP off buffs.... Is it right or not???</span><hr size=1> I generally only pay about 20 to 30 plat for a C3.<br>
<br>
However, the last time I checked I didn't pay much more than that for the rez spell.<br>
<br>
However, current price for the KEI is about 10 K.<br>
<br>
Kinda relative. You would have to C3 a lot of people to recoup that kinda plat.<br>
<br>
There is nothing wrong with charging for a rez, however, keep in mind you chose to get C3...the guy who died probably didn't chose that. Also kinda relative to hassle factor. Will your group be out of fighting for a while because you are spending mana on rezzes. Do you have to pay a porter to take you to a zone and buff you with SOE so you can make it to SEB easily before the timer runs out? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/btherathetravelagency.showUserPublicProfile?gid=dovelyngoldenheart>Dovelyn Goldenheart</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Less post, m0 play!</span><br>  Posts: 931<br> <font color=#00FFFF>(4/30/03 5:43 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1167.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: MAkeing PP off buffs.... Is it right or not???</span><hr size=1> I only have one comment:<br>
<br>
If people are going to ask for buffs that require components, they should at the very least offer to make up the cost of the component(s).<br>
<br>
Here's a guide:<br>
<br>
Group Aego - 42pp minimum<br>
Group Virtue - 21pp minimum<br>
Single Aego/Virtue/Symbol - 10.5pp minimum<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#222222><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/btherathetravelagency.showUserPublicProfile?gid=jurrasicepoch>Jurrasic Epoch</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_magentaspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>FK Rep</span><br>  Posts: 1042<br> <font color=#00FFFF>(4/30/03 5:46 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1167.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://thegeekhost.com/gravedirt/friend.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: MAkeing PP off buffs.... Is it right or not???</span><hr size=1> Making PP off buffs is a good thing, supply and demand and all that. if ima hunting in the planes alone, I want virtue NOW and I will be more then willing to pay well for it. <br>
<br>
Rezzes are a bit of a different ball of wax. it's one thing to say '50pp for a virtue' and if the person declines he's no worse off then he was before, but if a person is staring at hours of lost xp and someone says '50pp or you can /gofuk' and you stand to lose that xp that's quite a bit shittier to do, and that action will stay with your reputation forever. (Witness Kamar, aka K-mart)<br>
<br>
Personally, if I am dead in a bad spot and a cleric (non guildie of course) is able to spare me the cost of an EE to rez myself, I tend to give em at least 100pp or a nice gem anyhow afterwords.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/btherathetravelagency.showUserPublicProfile?gid=desseray>desseray</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 23<br> <font color=#00FFFF>(4/30/03 6:03 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1167.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: MAkeing PP off buffs.... Is it right or not???</span><hr size=1> I don't mind that people charge for buffs... just as long as they don't spam the zone out *cough* Brimely *cough*. Hitting your 'buffs'4'cash' hotkey every 15 seconds is just damn annoying.<br>
<br>
On the same note, don't abuse people when they DO buff w/o charging. Asking someone to wait 2 mins ( read: 15 mins) for your friend to come, is sorta... not nice. I've mgb'd clar quite a few times, and their is always those 1 or 2 people who /bitztell you cause they missed it and *you didn't wait* <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#222222><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/btherathetravelagency.showUserPublicProfile?gid=snwbdr94>Snwbdr94</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 9<br> <font color=#00FFFF>(4/30/03 8:24 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1167.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: MAkeing PP off buffs.... Is it right or not???</span><hr size=1> i pay 100pp for each rez i get and 100pp for corpse summon and depends on how much Cash i have for c3 i pay from 15pp to 100pp depends on my mood. but yea i am a nice guy i pay 50 to 75 for vitue/aego + 3 dots. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/btherathetravelagency.showUserPublicProfile?gid=joekreeper1>joekreeper1</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Toade, remember them?</span><br>  Posts: 411<br> <font color=#00FFFF>(4/30/03 8:57 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1167.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: MAkeing PP off buffs.... Is it right or not???</span><hr size=1> Paying/charging for buffs is fine, very few people would be getting Aego, C3, ect. on demand, if a caster couldnt make money for sitting in one spot for a long time rather than Xping or farming.<br>
<br>
way back when Kunark was new I died pick pocketing the note for the rogue epic in Kaladim... i was still bound in Nfreeport I paid a Cleric 1.5K to travel from DL (on his way to Seb) to kaladim to Rez me cause back then XP in the 50's was brutal and he had to travel so far to do it... so it's supply and demand I guess <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#222222><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/btherathetravelagency.showUserPublicProfile?gid=vaeldayanie>vaeldayanie</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 9<br> <font color=#00FFFF>(5/1/03 7:16 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1167.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: MAkeing PP off buffs.... Is it right or not???</span><hr size=1> Last I saw getting buffs/rezzes were not a requirement to play the game.  It is a service and therefore compensation should at least be offered.  I love paying for buffs.  I remember life before c3, c4, and c5, and i never want to go back.  <br>
<br>
The pp that these people make encourages them to come and give buffs which enhances my play experience by reducing my downtime.  This also enhances my guildies play experience because I dont have to bother them for the buffs.  I just have to cough up a few pp's.  Really, how long does it take to make 50-100pp?  15 minutes on a bad day?<br>
<br>
Vaeldayanie <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/btherathetravelagency.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kunoichiryuujin>Kunoichi Ryuujin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 12<br> <font color=#00FFFF>(5/1/03 7:54 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1167.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: MAkeing PP off buffs.... Is it right or not???</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>It is a service and therefore compensation should at least be offered.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
/agrees<br>
<br>
Well its your time...how you spend it in game is your choice... you make of it what you will.  <br>
<br>
You can go sit in a zone doing nothing but spaming for a group or you can sit in the Nexus LFG while making some plat at the same time.  <br>
<br>
Chanter spell c3 is very expensive to buy even with the new LoY research.  I always donate something in return for their time and mana.  After all I couldnt kill half the mobs I do without that &quot;buff&quot;.   And Cleric buffs cost regents, Rezzes much mana, unless that person wants to supply the regent or plat to cover the cost I wont buff them either unless they are my tank in an xp group. Druids ...well its comes down to time and mana.  I dont mind buffing lowbies (for free) I still do it alot but not as often as I once did. <br>
<br>
~ Kuno<br>
