g me. The amount varies. Might be whatever I have, up to 50pp. <br>
<br>
It just seems to be more respectful to say &quot;I'll gladly pay for the rez.&quot; Just shows you value their time. <br>
<br>
If I was a Cleric, I doubt I'd charge for rezzes. Buffs that use components, yes. But those would be reserved for groups or raids, and of course, you can't charge for those.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#222222><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/btherathetravelagency.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kathartic>Kathartic</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>DHG - GL</span><br>  Posts: 23<br> <font color=#00FFFF>(5/1/03 12:56 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1167.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: MAkeing PP off buffs.... Is it right or not???</span><hr size=1> When donating for buffs consider that if there is substantial profit in it for the caster, there will be a bigger supply of the buff available.  If there is little profit to be made then people casting these buffs are not going to use their time casting buffs hence a lower supply.<br>
<br>
Also the larger donations are noticed by some.  What this does is help you get those buffs even when someone is not doing some buffs for donations.  If you drop 75-100pp on the enchanter for that KEI, next time you need one and find that there isn't someone sitting around casting for donations, you might get a tell from that enchanter that is more than willing to cast it once even though they have no intention of sitting around for an hour in business so to speak.<br>
<br>
The whole buffing for donations thing seems a little messed up by those that feel they are entitled to the buffs.  This is especially true for rezzes since the whole GY thing was implemented.  Some folks expect an epic cleric to do this for them.  Most will anyway, but the expectation that they should get it makes it like you aren't even doing them a favor, but rather just doing your duty.  It becomes a less rewarding activity and less rewarding activities are avoided <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
Of course there is some reward in hearing the unsolicited excuse for a 1pp donation for a KEI from green con frog on a mount <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :lol --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/laugh.gif ALT=":lol"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Anyway, if one thinks it's greed that spurs the buff for donations market then I submit that maybe that one is in the expecation camp.  I see it as a generous behavior (the donation) begetting yet another generous act(the buff).  <br>
<br>
